Let's start counting heartbeats after the beat at time $\blue{t=0}$ seconds. Looking at the graph, we observe that $\blue{9}$ additional heartbeats occur within the first $\red{6}$ seconds.
To find the number of heartbeats in one minute, we proceed as follows.

$\qquad \displaystyle \dfrac{\blue{9} \ \textrm{beats} }{\red{6} \ \cancel{\textrm{sec}}} \cdot \dfrac{ \purple{60} \ \cancel{\textrm{sec}}}{1 \ \textrm{min}}
 = \dfrac{ 9  \cdot 60 \ \textrm{beats}}{ 6 \ \textrm{min}} 
=\dfrac{ 9  \cdot \cancel{6} \cdot 10 \ \textrm{beats}}{ \cancel{6} \ \textrm{min}} = 90$ beats per minute
